Of incredible rarity and made from exquisite materials, these helmets are a set of six, all designed to enhance one particular part of its wearer's strengths.

The elusive nature of its seller mark these as an oddity without history or origin, but old tombs and remains in the Amian region are sometimes found to be in possession of them, suggesting that they were used even in ancient times.

Made by the Order of the Dark Moon to give them a distinct advantage against those who are unaccustomed to fighting in the dark. These gloves are able to blind the victim temporarily, adding a whole new meaning to darkness.
Master Gloves of the Dark Moon
This item is not for PC use. If you have somehow come into possession of this, please contact a DM to have it removed and do not use it.
A very young and handsome man, this Adventurer can be very enthusiastic which often leads him to great perils though it seems he is very lucky.

This is a werewolf, no doubt about it. The stories speak of them, and now you see one in front of you, its teeth and claws covered in in the blood of its previous meal. It growls and bares its large, yellowed fangs towards you as if it were giving you the chance to flee. But that chance doesn't last long, and it bears down on all fours to charge at you before standing back up on two legs to slash at you with powerful claws and snap at you with a tremendous bite.

This wolf is much larger than something you'd expect to see in this forest, and with much dark fur and an oversized jaw to boot. When it sees you, it howls loudly, often in unison with other wolves in the pack, and immediately leaps to attack you, behavior that is distinctly unwolf-like and unprovoked. It fights with an intelligence far beyond that of a normal animal.

This grotesque creature seems all out of proportion. The head is large, with a maw full of sharp teeth, and a shape that looks vaguely like a cross between a rat and a human. The body itself is scrawny, ending in powerful, large hands and feet tipped with sharp claws. The creature's entire body looks dirty, as if it hadn't bathed in weeks. It is clearly a lycanthrope of some sort, probably a rodent.

This oversized rat screeches and bites at your ankles and fights in a manner that no typical rat ever should. It almost appears rabid, with foam dripping off of its mouth, filled with unnaturally sized fangs.

This lithe creature has a head resembling a cross between a panther and a human's face, with distinct whiskers poking out of slighlty puffy cheecks. The body is sinewy and flexible, and ends in powerful cat's paws. It tends to stay away from direct main combat, and instead you hear it speaking in an oddly human voice, calling down Druidic magics upon you. It is clearly a lycanthrope of some sort, probably a panther or a jaguar.

This panther has red blotches scattered about its fur that eerily resemble blood. It hangs back in combat, allows its packmates to do most of the upfront work. You hear it begin to grunt and make animal noises, and the next thing you know, a swirl of embers has risen up from it into the sky, and then rained back down on you in the form on a powerful Druidic spell. Clearly this is no plain cat!

This Lycanthrope is burly and over-muscular, so much that it appears to  be top heavy, with a huge chest and a very large head, topped with a wild mane, or ruff of thick coarse fur. Its tusks just out of its mouth, lending it the appearance of always being open to a degree. It growls loudly and charges at you, tusks first attempting to gore you with them before swinging a thick, pawed fist at your chest.

This creature is out of place to you, since boars don't often frequent forests. It also seems oversized, with tusks that appear too large, even for its face. Boars are notoriously territorial though, and this one is no exception... except instead of driving you off, this one seems to want to kill you. But boars aren't carnivorous. Right?

This person has a feral, savage look about them, wearing tattered clothes that look ruptured in unnatural ways, as if at one point it'd been worn by a person far too large for them, and it'd ripped when they'd attempted to put the clothes on. All of them seem intelligent, but with distinctly animalistic features about them. Something seems very off about these people...

Feral, eyes stare out, bloodshot red on the brink of madness. This beast's fur is a glossy brown with bloodstains around the tusks and hands - both old and new. It is no normal Wereboar. This being is one of Malar's chosen children, living only to breed destruction and chaos with  a supernatural rage under his will!
OOC ring for all bosses, to protect against the more popular spells for instant death.
This mighty beast was re-animated with Dark Magic. Even being an undead, it retains it's ferocity!
This man have blue scales on all of his body, fangs, claws, slitted eyes and Blue Wings.

This man on his late thirties stands at six feet tall with raven black hair and eyes that are always keeping watch at his surroundings. His armour is adorned with symbols depicting his Faith of Selune and his Holy Symbol is aways at plain view.
This item is not for PC use. If you have somehow come into possession of this, please contact a DM to have it removed and do not use it.
